ster, Kadane tracks the transformation of Barker’s consciousness from a Puritan to an Enlightenment outlook, revealing through one man’s journey the large-scale shifts in self-understanding whose philosophical reverberations have shaped debates on human nature for centuries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aThe Enlightenment, Original Sin, Anthropological Faith, Human Nature, History of Political Thought, History of Capitalism, History of Christianity, Pentecost Barker, Microhistory, Intellectual History.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226832883423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226832883/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles